In fact, 11% of American citizens, or 21 million people in the age of voting, do not possess identity cards with photo issued by a government agency in their state.
Moreover, five million new voters in 2012 don’t have such a identity document.
But it often costs more than a hundred dollars to get the required identity card.
The new restrictions disproportionately affect young people, minorities, and low-income people.
