53% of the patients who are admitted to Victor-Gadbois home come from their home, 47% come from the hospital.
Access to palliative care
It is said that 77% of Canadians simply do not have access to palliative care, i.e. care designed to relieve suffering when a sick reaches the final phase of his life, whether it is at home, at the hospital or at home care.
