According to Palas, the EU had to pay us millions of euros, because the Czech Republic is far from the ports.
Finally, the European Commission responded positively to the Czech demand and organized an offer call for the purchase of wheat from countries without maritime access.
Subsidies for the obtaining of subsidies were proposed to the municipalities by the Ministry of Local Development led by Minister Pavel Němec (US-DEU), these should, concrete, serve to write the subsidy applications granted by Brussels.
The EU declares: “Strange regulations are rare.”
Although regulations often raise criticism in the Member States, according to many experts, the EU’s efforts to regulate and improve the effectiveness of the functioning of the Union as well as in the field of its overall development are rather worthy of praise.
More serious is, for example, according to experts, the problem of the use of EU subsidies for projects that have absolutely nothing to do with the strengthening of European integration, but which have been imposed by the Member States during the budget talks.
