What are the symptoms of a sexual illness?
Infectious diseases can cause abscesses in the genital organs, urinary pain, white loss, pain in the lower end, as well as the appearance of buttons and verrues.
However, they do not regularly cause any pain or other symptoms and therefore remain hidden.
How to protect yourself?
Condoms can reduce the risk of infection, but they do not protect to 100%.
The reason is that the pathogens of sexually transmitted diseases can also be transmitted by lubricating infection or through close body contacts.
Experts therefore recommend that anyone who often changes sexual partners regularly pass tests.
Most rapidly detected ISTs can be healed and late sequels can be avoided.
