For four euros, Indonesian volcano carriers risk their lives and health by carrying 70 pounds of sulfur through sharp stone trails.
There are people for whom work is hell and others who literally work in hell.
This is the case of Anto Wijaya, one of the 400 miners who earn their lives by carrying sulfur from the Kawah Ijen volcano, east of the Indonesian island of Java.
