It then sells it for 10,000 rubles (83 cents) to the petrochemical industry since this mineral is very present in everyday life and is used to make candles, fireworks, cosmetics, dynamite and even serves to whiten sugar.
“As we carry about 70 pounds, we earn about 46,000 rupees (3.8 euros) on each trip,” Anto explains, who generally carries three trips a day.
